00:52:40.830 --> 00:52:42.990
Abu Sufyan says, yes, he has a good lineage.

00:52:42.990 --> 00:52:44.950
Obviously, he just said he was a relative.

00:52:44.950 --> 00:52:47.510
So it has to be a good lineage.

00:52:47.510 --> 00:52:49.390
He says, yes, he has a good lineage.

00:52:49.390 --> 00:52:51.190
He says thereafter, he says,

00:52:51.190 --> 00:52:53.630
has anyone before him ever said something

00:52:53.630 --> 00:52:55.310
similar to what he has said?

00:52:55.310 --> 00:52:56.510
Abu Sufyan said, no,

00:52:56.510 --> 00:52:58.550
he's the first one who came with it.

00:52:58.550 --> 00:53:00.310
Have there been any kings or leaders

00:53:00.310 --> 00:53:01.910
from his parents or family?

00:53:01.910 --> 00:53:02.750
No.

00:53:04.030 --> 00:53:05.190
Thereafter, he says,

00:53:05.190 --> 00:53:07.710
have you ever considered him a liar in anything?

00:53:07.710 --> 00:53:08.750
Has he lied?

00:53:08.750 --> 00:53:10.430
No, he's not a liar.

00:53:10.430 --> 00:53:12.390
We never knew him as a liar.

00:53:12.390 --> 00:53:14.030
Then he says,

00:53:14.030 --> 00:53:16.430
have any of his forefathers uttered words

00:53:16.430 --> 00:53:17.270
similar to this?

00:53:17.270 --> 00:53:19.030
The answer is no.

00:53:19.030 --> 00:53:20.590
Who are the people who follow him?

00:53:20.590 --> 00:53:22.830
The wealthy or the influential

00:53:22.830 --> 00:53:24.710
or those who do not have much influence?

00:53:24.710 --> 00:53:25.550
He said, well,

00:53:25.550 --> 00:53:26.990
those who don't have much influence

00:53:26.990 --> 00:53:28.270
are the ones who follow him.

00:53:28.270 --> 00:53:30.110
Then he says,

00:53:30.110 --> 00:53:31.790
are the numbers of his followers

00:53:31.790 --> 00:53:33.430
increasing or decreasing?

00:53:33.430 --> 00:53:35.630
He says, well, they are increasing.

00:53:35.630 --> 00:53:36.590
Then he says,

00:53:36.590 --> 00:53:38.710
are people who have accepted his message

00:53:38.710 --> 00:53:41.950
ever reneging, coming back

00:53:41.950 --> 00:53:43.110
and rejecting the message?

00:53:43.110 --> 00:53:45.270
He says, not one of them.

00:53:45.270 --> 00:53:46.910
Then he says,

00:53:46.910 --> 00:53:48.630
does he ever break his promise

00:53:48.630 --> 00:53:51.310
and his treaty when he promises?

00:53:51.310 --> 00:53:52.750
He says, no, never.

00:53:52.750 --> 00:53:54.150
In fact, right now we are here

00:53:54.150 --> 00:53:55.910
because of a treaty we have with him.

00:53:55.910 --> 00:53:57.230
That's what he says.

00:53:57.230 --> 00:54:00.900
Then he says,

00:54:00.900 --> 00:54:02.580
have you ever fought him?

00:54:02.580 --> 00:54:03.540
And if you have,

00:54:03.540 --> 00:54:05.100
what is the result of the war?

00:54:05.100 --> 00:54:07.140
He says, well, we have fought him.

00:54:07.140 --> 00:54:09.260
One war he wins, one war we win.

00:54:09.260 --> 00:54:11.580
One war he wins, one war we win.

00:54:11.580 --> 00:54:12.980
So this man was convinced.

00:54:12.980 --> 00:54:14.580
He says, wallahi,

00:54:14.580 --> 00:54:17.140
if what you are telling me is true,

00:54:17.140 --> 00:54:18.780
then he is the messenger

00:54:18.780 --> 00:54:20.100
that we are waiting for.

00:54:20.100 --> 00:54:21.380
But I did not expect him

00:54:21.380 --> 00:54:22.940
to be from amongst the Arabs.

00:54:22.940 --> 00:54:23.780
And wallahi,

00:54:23.780 --> 00:54:25.540
if what you are saying is true,

00:54:25.540 --> 00:54:28.020
he will very soon rule the piece of land

00:54:28.020 --> 00:54:29.700
under my feet.

00:54:29.700 --> 00:54:30.460
That's what he says.

00:54:30.460 --> 00:54:31.500
Who?

00:54:31.500 --> 00:54:34.580
From the Roman Empire, Heraclius.

00:54:34.580 --> 00:54:35.820
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:54:35.820 --> 00:54:38.780
grant us an understanding.

00:54:38.780 --> 00:54:40.220
In fact, he also asked a question,

00:54:40.220 --> 00:54:41.260
what does he command?

00:54:41.260 --> 00:54:42.740
What does he instruct?

00:54:42.740 --> 00:54:44.940
So Abu Sufyan says,

00:54:44.940 --> 00:54:47.700
he instructs us, first thing,

00:54:47.700 --> 00:54:50.220
an ta'budu allaha wahdahu laa sharika lah.

00:54:50.220 --> 00:54:52.020
laa tushariku billahi shay'an.

00:54:52.020 --> 00:54:53.500
To worship Allah alone

00:54:53.500 --> 00:54:55.500
without associating partners

00:54:55.500 --> 00:54:57.260
with Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:54:57.260 --> 00:54:59.540
If you take a careful look at that answer,

00:54:59.540 --> 00:55:01.660
the first thing Abu Sufyan is saying,

00:55:01.660 --> 00:55:03.980
the Prophet was worried about shirk.

00:55:03.980 --> 00:55:07.460
Nobody must engage in association

00:55:07.460 --> 00:55:09.860
of partnership with Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:55:09.860 --> 00:55:10.860
This was Muhammad,

00:55:10.860 --> 00:55:12.940
sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:55:12.940 --> 00:55:14.500
So up to this day,

00:55:14.500 --> 00:55:15.860
the prime message of Islam,

00:55:15.860 --> 00:55:17.180
worship Allah alone,

00:55:17.180 --> 00:55:19.140
do not associate any partners

00:55:19.140 --> 00:55:21.300
with Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:55:21.300 --> 00:55:25.380
Now, this man says to Abu Sufyan,

00:55:25.380 --> 00:55:28.260
you see, I asked you about his lineage,

00:55:28.260 --> 00:55:30.780
because the messengers come with a good lineage.

00:55:30.780 --> 00:55:31.900
I asked you,

00:55:31.900 --> 00:55:34.620
if anyone before him has said anything of this nature,

00:55:34.620 --> 00:55:37.220
because perhaps he would just be following them.

00:55:37.220 --> 00:55:38.860
I asked you about his forefathers,

00:55:38.860 --> 00:55:41.180
because if his forefathers were leaders or kings,

00:55:41.180 --> 00:55:43.300
perhaps he just wanted to gain it back.

00:55:43.300 --> 00:55:44.940
I asked you if anyone,

00:55:44.940 --> 00:55:46.940
I asked you if anyone called him a liar

00:55:46.940 --> 00:55:48.420
or if he was a liar.

00:55:48.420 --> 00:55:49.540
When you said no,

00:55:49.540 --> 00:55:52.420
I knew that if he does not lie about people,

00:55:52.420 --> 00:55:54.900
he would never lie about the Almighty.

00:55:54.900 --> 00:55:56.060
Subhanallah, simple.

00:55:56.060 --> 00:55:58.060
If a man doesn't lie between one another,

00:55:58.060 --> 00:56:00.780
why would he lie about Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala?

00:56:00.780 --> 00:56:02.580
Then I asked you about his followers,

00:56:02.580 --> 00:56:04.140
because all the messengers,

00:56:04.140 --> 00:56:06.780
the followers, their followers primarily

00:56:06.780 --> 00:56:08.980
are those who are not that influential.

00:56:08.980 --> 00:56:10.420
And thereafter, I asked you,

00:56:10.420 --> 00:56:12.020
do they increase or decrease?

00:56:12.020 --> 00:56:14.700
Because as the Iman increases,

00:56:14.700 --> 00:56:16.780
nobody would actually go back

00:56:16.780 --> 00:56:19.260
and the numbers would never ever decrease.

00:56:19.260 --> 00:56:21.620
And thereafter, I asked you about

00:56:21.620 --> 00:56:22.980
whether he breaks promises,

00:56:22.980 --> 00:56:25.300
because a messenger does not break a promise.

00:56:25.300 --> 00:56:26.820
And I asked you if you fight him,

00:56:26.820 --> 00:56:27.860
and who wins?

00:56:27.860 --> 00:56:29.460
And all the messengers,

00:56:29.460 --> 00:56:30.900
they win and they lose,

00:56:30.900 --> 00:56:32.100
they win and they lose,

00:56:32.100 --> 00:56:34.460
but final victory is theirs.

00:56:34.460 --> 00:56:35.460
Do you know what happened?

00:56:35.460 --> 00:56:36.980
The people around Heraclius

00:56:36.980 --> 00:56:38.540
began to make a noise

00:56:38.540 --> 00:56:40.180
to the degree that they had to

00:56:40.180 --> 00:56:42.020
send Abu Sufyan and them out

00:56:42.020 --> 00:56:43.860
and they were discussing amongst themselves

00:56:43.860 --> 00:56:45.060
whatever they discussed.

00:56:45.060 --> 00:56:47.780
Abu Sufyan later on himself says

00:56:47.780 --> 00:56:50.300
that I told my people of Quraysh

00:56:50.300 --> 00:56:51.900
at that particular time

00:56:51.940 --> 00:56:53.940
that you see this Ibn Abi Kabsha,

00:56:53.940 --> 00:56:55.420
that was the name they used to use

00:56:55.420 --> 00:56:57.020
for Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wa sallam.

00:56:57.020 --> 00:56:59.700
He says, you see even the Roman king

00:56:59.700 --> 00:57:00.620
is fearing him.

00:57:00.620 --> 00:57:01.740
Look at this,

00:57:01.740 --> 00:57:03.860
even the Roman king is fearing him.

00:57:03.860 --> 00:57:05.660
And Abu Sufyan says later on

00:57:05.660 --> 00:57:06.900
that it was at that point

00:57:06.900 --> 00:57:08.540
when I felt in my heart

00:57:08.540 --> 00:57:11.460
the first effect of Islam.

00:57:11.460 --> 00:57:13.260
See, he didn't accept Islam at that stage,

00:57:13.260 --> 00:57:14.340
Abu Sufyan.

00:57:14.340 --> 00:57:16.900
But this man Heraclius

00:57:16.900 --> 00:57:18.380
who did not accept Islam,

00:57:18.380 --> 00:57:19.500
but he had a discussion,

00:57:19.500 --> 00:57:21.500
he knew this is right.

00:57:21.500 --> 00:57:23.260
So when Heraclius met his leaders

00:57:23.260 --> 00:57:25.140
in Himes a little bit later on,

00:57:25.140 --> 00:57:26.420
he had a meeting with them,

00:57:26.420 --> 00:57:27.460
all his chiefs,

00:57:27.460 --> 00:57:28.580
he closed the doors

00:57:28.580 --> 00:57:29.700
and he told them look,

00:57:29.700 --> 00:57:30.540
there is a messenger,

00:57:30.540 --> 00:57:31.980
he gave them the story.

00:57:31.980 --> 00:57:33.620
They were so upset,

00:57:33.620 --> 00:57:35.180
they all rushed to the door,

00:57:35.180 --> 00:57:36.940
they found it locked.

00:57:36.940 --> 00:57:38.300
When they got back,

00:57:38.300 --> 00:57:39.660
he told them relax,

00:57:39.660 --> 00:57:40.540
take it easy.

00:57:40.540 --> 00:57:41.820
I'm not telling it to you

00:57:41.820 --> 00:57:43.820
because I want to follow him.

00:57:43.820 --> 00:57:45.020
I'm telling it to you

00:57:45.020 --> 00:57:47.980
to see how seriously you take your faith.

00:57:47.980 --> 00:57:48.620
So don't worry,

00:57:48.620 --> 00:57:49.980
we're not going to follow him.

00:57:49.980 --> 00:57:51.220
Look at this.

00:57:51.220 --> 00:57:53.380
After knowing what was right and wrong,

00:57:53.380 --> 00:57:56.460
after asking the questions,

00:57:56.460 --> 00:57:57.620
he still did not accept.

00:57:57.620 --> 00:57:59.180
And this is why we say

00:57:59.180 --> 00:58:01.140
and I want to end on this note,

00:58:01.140 --> 00:58:03.060
my beloved brothers and sisters,

00:58:03.060 --> 00:58:05.140
we know what is right.

00:58:05.140 --> 00:58:06.820
We know what we have is right.

00:58:06.820 --> 00:58:08.100
We don't have a doubt.

00:58:08.100 --> 00:58:10.100
Why is it that we take so long?

00:58:10.100 --> 00:58:11.740
We take so long to leave that

00:58:11.740 --> 00:58:13.380
which will earn the wrath of Allah,

00:58:13.380 --> 00:58:14.820
our bad habits.

00:58:14.820 --> 00:58:16.500
We take so long to leave them.

00:58:16.500 --> 00:58:18.220
Why is it that we cannot leave sin

00:58:18.220 --> 00:58:19.380
for the sake of Allah

00:58:19.380 --> 00:58:20.300
when what we have,

00:58:20.300 --> 00:58:21.660
we know it is right.

00:58:21.660 --> 00:58:23.180
We take so long to respond.

00:58:23.180 --> 00:58:24.980
Why is it that we feel lazy

00:58:24.980 --> 00:58:26.860
to obey the instruction of Allah?

00:58:26.860 --> 00:58:29.260
We couldn't even cover ourselves

00:58:29.260 --> 00:58:31.100
to save our lives sometimes.

00:58:31.100 --> 00:58:33.340
May Allah safeguard our women.

00:58:33.340 --> 00:58:34.700
Sometimes we have a scarf,

00:58:34.700 --> 00:58:35.780
a piece of cloth,

00:58:35.780 --> 00:58:36.900
which is so small,

00:58:36.900 --> 00:58:38.420
which could be the result

00:58:38.420 --> 00:58:39.700
of our entry into Jannah

00:58:39.700 --> 00:58:42.020
or it could result in our entry into Jannah.

00:58:42.020 --> 00:58:43.420
And perhaps we have just flung it

00:58:43.420 --> 00:58:44.460
into our wardrobe

00:58:44.460 --> 00:58:45.500
and we walk out

00:58:45.500 --> 00:58:48.100
in the total wrath of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:58:48.100 --> 00:58:49.980
We take so long to respond.

00:58:49.980 --> 00:58:51.620
Come on, shouldn't the hearts

00:58:51.620 --> 00:58:53.460
of the Muslims soften up?

00:58:53.460 --> 00:58:55.220
We don't want to be like Heraclius

00:58:55.220 --> 00:58:57.260
and the others who knew what was right

00:58:57.260 --> 00:58:58.100
and what was wrong,

00:58:58.100 --> 00:59:00.020
but they rejected it.

00:59:00.020 --> 00:59:01.700
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us

00:59:01.700 --> 00:59:02.540
the surrendering.

00:59:02.540 --> 00:59:03.660
Insha'Allah we meet tomorrow

00:59:03.660 --> 00:59:04.860
to continue with this,

00:59:04.860 --> 00:59:05.700
until then.
